    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a concentrated offensive core, anchored by **Luis Robert Jr.**, who carries our highest efficiency score of 75.158. He represents our strongest play, benefiting from a significant platoon advantage against the left-handed Rodriguez and the favorable lineup placement in the three-hole, which outweighs the slight park penalty. Meanwhile, **Jacob Wilson** remains a high-floor asset at 64.54, capitalizing on a lead-off spot against Weathers that provides essential opportunities for Runs and SB, the latter being our most critical scarcity target. **Jackson Merrill** also clears our \"Strong\" threshold at 60.44; despite a middling matchup against Herget, his projected efficiency remains solid enough to warrant inclusion in the utility slot to maximize our daily cap utility.\n\nOur toughest roster decision centered on **Liam Hicks**, who fell just shy of the lineup with a score of 39.83. While he projected for a decent platoon edge against Lowder, the underlying skill metrics of the opposing starter created enough drag to push **Liam Hicks** below our 40-point \"Zebras Floor.\" Consequently, we are keeping our bats tight today, especially as we navigate an off-day for cornerstones like **Kyle Tucker**, **Gunnar Henderson**, and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** We continue to monitor the status of **Andy Pages**, **Jordan Westburg**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Drake Baldwin**, **Josh Lowe**, **Heliot Ramos**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Marcell Ozuna**, **Josh Jung**, **Coby Mayo**, and **Nolan Schanuel** for potential late-week rotation shifts. For today, **Miguel Vargas** rounds out the starters at 57.21; while he faces a formidable opponent in Lugo, his place in the three-hole offers enough R and RBI upside to justify the start despite the slight drag from the opponent's high-efficiency hold ability.",
